reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Great AUD recording quality, occasionally interrupted by the garbled cries of a guy who drank a case a beer before walking in the gates. 

No highlights in set 1. Jerry not really taking the lead. Vince does his best to make up for it. Cassidy is pretty okay, I guess? Decent singing throughout. 

Set 2 is where it is at. Big Railroad Blues (rare)! Easily the best Playin' in the Band in '94 to-date. Super UJB as well. Pretty boring Drums>Space. FIRST SAMBA IN THE RAIN...WOOOOOO. Nice SOTM.

I Fought the Law might be the best-played song of '94.
